    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverioDAI1"/>, p. 98, n. <citedRange>33</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.34</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>013600</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, pp. <citedRange>300-301</citedRange>, number 41, fragment b (text)</bibl>.</p>                    
            <p>For a general bibliography on the accounts of the damiergoi see <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr011400</ref>.
                </p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <w lemma="λοιπός"><supplied reason="lost">Λοιπὸν</supplied></w> 
                        <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <num type="total" atLeast="1.2">
                                <measure type="currency" unit="drachma">
                                    <num value="1"><g type="cyrnum">Ζ</g></num>
                                    <num value="0.2"><g type="cyrnum">&gt;</g></num></measure></num>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>. 
                    <w lemma="παρόρεγμα"><supplied reason="lost">Πα</supplied>ρόρ<lb n="3" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost">εγμα</supplied></w> <rs type="office" key="damiergos"><w lemma="δαμιεργός"><supplied reason="lost">δαμιεργοῖς</supplied></w></rs> 
                        <w lemma="μνᾶ"><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>μ</abbr><ex>ναῖ</ex></expan></supplied></w>
                        <num type="total" value="300">
                        <measure type="currency" unit="drachma">
                            <num type="total" value="3">
                                <measure type="currency" unit="mna">
                                    <num value="1"><unclear><g type="cyrnum">–</g></unclear></num>
                                    <num value="1"><unclear><g type="cyrnum">–</g></unclear></num>
                                    <num value="1"><g type="cyrnum">–</g></num></measure></num></measure></num>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">Reste</supplied>: <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> 1 drachme 1 obole. Indemnité <supplied reason="lost">pour les 
            démiurges</supplied> 3 mines.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">Remainder</supplied>: <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> 1 drachma 1 obol. Allowance <supplied reason="lost">for the 
            damiergoi</supplied> 3 mines.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">Resto</supplied>: <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> 1 dracma 1 obolo. Retribuzione <supplied reason="lost">per i damiurghi</supplied> 3 mine.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>[---] [المتبقي]: [---] 1 دراخما و1 أوبول. يُعطى [للداميرجوي] 3 ميناي.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Line 1, the sign for 1/5 drachma (= 1 obol), instead of being angular, has on that stone a lunate shape, like at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr012500</ref>. For this reason and 
                for some others, we do not join this fragment with <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr011900</ref>, in spite of <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl>'s tantalizing 
                suggestion (see commentary ad locum).</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
